configset  GLOBAL  comments <<TAG
[VALUE LINES]
TAG
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
configset listname comments <<TAG
[VALUE LINES]
TAG
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value : no default
Data Type     : string_array
Category      : miscellany
Password Notes: Visible only with password. 
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset GLOBAL comments << ENDTAG
9 May 1999 - initial creation of list
ENDTAG


$INCLUDE-config/comments

The comments setting is used in configuration templates to provide
instructions.  For example, the DEFAULT:personal template has
instructions for applying the other settings in the template to a
mailing list with the configset command.


See Also:
   help admin_config   (for a description of configuration templates)
   help here_document

$INCLUDE-help/foot
